race.comment: Small field to begin the day. TENNESSEE SPIRIT (5) was most impressive at the trials coming into this, showing plenty of speed over 400m at this track. The 1000m journey and inside draw looks a recipe for success on resumption with Parnham sticking from the trial. Looks the one to beat. LADIES PRO (2) has been effective in a couple of short course trials leading into her debut, though it wouldn't surprise me if she got over further in time. Fiore road her in her latest trial where she stuck on well to the line. Ticks a few boxes and looks the main danger. CALL ME INVINCIBLE (1) is fitter for three trials coming into this and remains a Colt heading into this 3YO season. He's drawn well under Brad Parnham and he can make his presence felt. NINETYMILESTRAIGHT (3) is not out of this if she can improve on the fresh run. SWEET ISSY (4) is next best.
